	<body>
		<outline text="August 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="august2021" >
			<outline text="August 7" type="calendarDay" name="07" >
				<outline text="Awesome! Let us know if you have any feedback or suggestions! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/curtaindsleep/status/1423918409578958854&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 08:08:27 GMT" tweetId="1423918950832742401" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1423918950832742401" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Thank you! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/nabhan_yt/status/1423747069991395338&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 08:03:15 GMT" tweetId="1423917641727500298" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1423917641727500298" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Thank you for the shout-out! There're many things to explore in the future, but I'm super happy that it works for the way you work! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/fncll/status/1423765441000792066&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 08:02:56 GMT" tweetId="1423917563734413316" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1423917563734413316" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 6" type="calendarDay" name="06" >
				<outline text="🥰 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/The_Coder_Vet/status/1423675549931687941&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 16:20:56 GMT" tweetId="1423680501441646600" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1423680501441646600" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Thanks! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TfTCreator/status/1423672806236172288&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 16:20:39 GMT" tweetId="1423680428762755077" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1423680428762755077" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Full changelog at &lt;a href=&quot;https://logseq.github.io/#/page/f3b8092e-ab5c-42c9-883c-81ae055b051d&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/AhMtzsE09R" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 15:24:02 GMT" tweetId="1423666182075289608" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1423666182075289608" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="PDF highlighter is out 📖✍️
Some features:
1. text highlight
2. area highlight (press either Cmd/Ctrl or Alt)
3. dark/light themes
4. click highlight reference to jump back to PDF.

Gif demo:
&lt;a href=&quot;https://logseq.github.io/assets/2021-08-06_21.46.20_1628257857150_0.gif&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

Download: https://t.co/ZOuXPnXd9b https://t.co/6dXF77vbCF" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 15:22:29 GMT" tweetId="1423665790134349826" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1423665790134349826" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Today's card! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1423581905425891340/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 09:49:09 GMT" tweetId="1423581905425891340" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1423581905425891340" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="😄 Wonderful tweaks! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/hrdcrpxxx/status/1422954794617131008&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 09:24:40 GMT" tweetId="1423575742831423490" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1423575742831423490" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Very cool! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/szal_ai/status/1423395381292027913&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 07:11:28 GMT" tweetId="1423542221991673859" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1423542221991673859" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 3" type="calendarDay" name="03" >
				<outline text="Our existing backend code is open sourced on GitHub, it's mostly for people who'd like to self-host the GitHub integration themselves.
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/logseq/deprecated-github-backend&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;
Notice that we have no plan to open-source the future backend for both data safety and business considerations." type="tweet" created="Tue, 03 Aug 2021 15:33:49 GMT" tweetId="1422581480912420873" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1422581480912420873" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="0.3.1 is out! 
Some highlights:
1. Performance should be much better when editing long pages
2. Jump to alias's source page when searching
3. Remove key from the page title #zotero
4. PDF attachment link not working #zotero
5. Static export fails if an asset is missing &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1422581178582724609/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 03 Aug 2021 15:32:37 GMT" tweetId="1422581178582724609" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1422581178582724609" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 2" type="calendarDay" name="02" >
				<outline text="Your wife is always right! 🤣 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/laialai/status/1422238788399501315&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 03 Aug 2021 01:59:18 GMT" tweetId="1422376498795749379" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1422376498795749379" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="The most beautiful thing that has happened so far! This is exactly what we built Logseq for! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ARossP/status/1422239064972046342&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 03 Aug 2021 01:51:21 GMT" tweetId="1422374496737001474" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1422374496737001474" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Thanks! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/melikedonertas/status/1422209502053601284&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 15:55:26 GMT" tweetId="1422224531129655305" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1422224531129655305" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/JulioNavr/status/1422206905817223168&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/8iw7xR8F8v" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 15:53:21 GMT" tweetId="1422224004815855618" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1422224004815855618" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Incredible unofficial Logseq Documentation by &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mschmidtkorth&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;! 😱

https://t.co/WsdcyCBwAv

Source pages: https://t.co/leiWo9bjma https://t.co/ePvlxlsIlb" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 04:35:48 GMT" tweetId="1422053495205552130" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1422053495205552130" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 1" type="calendarDay" name="01" >
				<outline text="Thank you for the kind words! @kanru contributed the encryption part! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/sai_prasanna/status/1421772810851012611&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 16:25:37 GMT" tweetId="1421869740033597441" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1421869740033597441" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="SRS cards, Zotero integration, and PDF annotations are for people who enjoy learning or who gave up Anki because it's too hard to make cards. All those features are developed, our focus will be on bugs, UX enhancements, and mobile apps. 
Also, real-time collaboration!" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 09:42:17 GMT" tweetId="1421768236404600836" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1421768236404600836" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Ok, a preview for our &quot;last&quot; big feature! 😄 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/nabhan_yt/status/1421197030886711303&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/qC7wztX3mJ" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 09:25:11 GMT" tweetId="1421763933782765570" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1421763933782765570" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Thank you Julio! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/JulioNavr/status/1421470444759232518&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 08:59:15 GMT" tweetId="1421757408318148608" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1421757408318148608" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Thanks! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/curtaindsleep/status/1421381038580903939&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 08:53:47 GMT" tweetId="1421756031886008321" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1421756031886008321" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Thank you! 
We have some early feedback so that we made some changes, for example, removing the &quot;_key&quot; from the page title and put &quot;Abstract&quot; to a separate block, those will be in the next release! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/AlixLahuec/status/1421133692500692993&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 08:36:28 GMT" tweetId="1421751673181990914" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1421751673181990914" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="July 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="july2021" >
			<outline text="July 30" type="calendarDay" name="30" >
				<outline text="@zotero rocks! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/gabriheinrichs/status/1421128564301352964&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 15:31:36 GMT" tweetId="1421131369254559746" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1421131369254559746" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="This plugin took the idea and inspiration from the great zotero-roam made by @AlixLahuec. Special thanks to @AlixLahuec for providing all kinds of ideas and useful suggestions!
The documentation is at &lt;a href=&quot;https://logseq.github.io/#/page/Zotero&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/ss52TQrZF1" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 14:58:14 GMT" tweetId="1421122972954202121" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1421122972954202121" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="0.3.0 is just out!
Some highlights:
1. Zotero integration! 🥳🥳
    Type /zotero to start!
2. Support == for highlight in Markdown
3. Add /Embed Twitter support! (by @pengx17)
4. Fixed broken block references after refreshing
5. Fixed page references not working &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1421122418043625472/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 14:56:02 GMT" tweetId="1421122418043625472" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1421122418043625472" tweetUserName="logseq" >
					<outline text="Full changelog at &lt;a href=&quot;https://logseq.github.io/#/page/f65e2408-643d-43af-9320-57f1076847d5&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 14:56:21 GMT" tweetId="1421122496888115200" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1421122496888115200" inReplyToId="1421122418043625472" tweetUserName="logseq" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Yes, you can add `:default-home {:page &quot;My home page&quot;}` to your config.edn file. Replace `My home page` with your page name. More examples can be found at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/logseq/logseq/blob/master/templates/config.edn#L40&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/FJnBe7Bj3Y https://t.co/b5Rh43PsVI" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 10:02:35 GMT" tweetId="1421048568312307718" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1421048568312307718" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="It feels so good to see so many interests in Datalog! Join us if you're interested too! &lt;a href=&quot;https://discord.com/invite/KpN4eHY&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/BV1abqkSYp" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 04:42:57 GMT" tweetId="1420968129987969026" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1420968129987969026" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 29" type="calendarDay" name="29" >
				<outline text="PR merged! 🎉🎉 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/JulioNavr/status/1420912528260046853&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 01:26:42 GMT" tweetId="1420918744658833412" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1420918744658833412" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 27" type="calendarDay" name="27" >
				<outline text="Pretty mindmap! 🎉🎉 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/vipzhicheng/status/1419893209338048512&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/VTh037VUBi" type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 05:40:50 GMT" tweetId="1419895536467931136" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1419895536467931136" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 26" type="calendarDay" name="26" >
				<outline text="0.2.10 is just out!
Some highlights:
1. Long pages should be loading faster
2. Query results support both nested children and breadcrumbs
3. Both `^^` and `__` can be auto paired when there's selected text
4. fix crash when auto-complete some page references
5. org-mode id links &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1419705524136779782/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 26 Jul 2021 17:05:48 GMT" tweetId="1419705524136779782" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1419705524136779782" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Wow! Thank you very much for making this! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kris__kaminski/status/1419698524950773772&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 26 Jul 2021 16:49:35 GMT" tweetId="1419701445142536192" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1419701445142536192" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="That's a lot! Congrats!🥳 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/dasaptaerwin/status/1419647258933354501&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 26 Jul 2021 14:41:31 GMT" tweetId="1419669215804485633" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1419669215804485633" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 25" type="calendarDay" name="25" >
				<outline text="Thank you for the kind words! Looking forward to making Logseq more stable! 😄 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TfTHacker/status/1419251833831370752&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 25 Jul 2021 11:11:20 GMT" tweetId="1419253930270158852" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1419253930270158852" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Thanks! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/therayfdj/status/1419200441473241089&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 25 Jul 2021 08:43:23 GMT" tweetId="1419216700378009602" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1419216700378009602" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 24" type="calendarDay" name="24" >
				<outline text="Thanks! You can add this query to your &quot;Favorites&quot; in the right sidebar or any page.
{{query (task later now todo doing)}} &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/WillPlatnick/status/1418681592998940673&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/fur5KLieIW" type="tweet" created="Sun, 25 Jul 2021 03:54:40 GMT" tweetId="1419144041048903680" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1419144041048903680" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Thank you! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/JohnHamiltonNZ/status/1418942831637454868&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 25 Jul 2021 03:50:18 GMT" tweetId="1419142940736122884" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1419142940736122884" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 23" type="calendarDay" name="23" >
				<outline text="🎊 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/OneStuttering/status/1418300170576572417&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 23 Jul 2021 06:25:18 GMT" tweetId="1418457175559606274" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1418457175559606274" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 22" type="calendarDay" name="22" >
				<outline text="Do you want to review custom collections of your cards? Meet the`/cards` query!
&lt;a href=&quot;https://logseq.github.io/#/page/cards&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/bv5tLppiix" type="tweet" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 15:57:04 GMT" tweetId="1418238676107026434" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1418238676107026434" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="You can create some clozes too! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1418238165303713792/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 15:55:02 GMT" tweetId="1418238165303713792" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1418238165303713792" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="0.2.7 is just out! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1418237694535094272/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 15:53:10 GMT" tweetId="1418237694535094272" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1418237694535094272" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Memory fades, let me introduce the SRS cards! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1418237564515864580/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 15:52:39 GMT" tweetId="1418237564515864580" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1418237564515864580" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="How to use @Replit and @vercel to publish your Logseq notes? &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JVhGmpP4qpo&amp;ab_channel=PrashantSengar&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;
Shared by @prashanttgs 💯
https://t.co/OO4dFkjOSw" type="tweet" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 04:39:16 GMT" tweetId="1418068103032754179" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1418068103032754179" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 20" type="calendarDay" name="20" >
				<outline text="M-x logseq 😁 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/vsbabu/status/1417508182939762689&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 02:22:50 GMT" tweetId="1417671378853978112" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1417671378853978112" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 19" type="calendarDay" name="19" >
				<outline text="🤩 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/manojnayak/status/1417144590591696899&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 15:32:10 GMT" tweetId="1417145247583195136" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1417145247583195136" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="0.2.6 is just out!
You can download the desktop app at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/logseq/logseq/releases/tag/0.2.6&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;
Full changelog at https://t.co/laqQA9AQqW https://t.co/ynpfArweb5" type="tweet" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 14:11:42 GMT" tweetId="1417124995562541059" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1417124995562541059" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Time to enjoy a graph database! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1417124186389049344/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 14:08:29 GMT" tweetId="1417124186389049344" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1417124186389049344" tweetUserName="logseq" >
					<outline text="The function supports some aggregations like sum/average/min/max/total, thanks to sci (by @borkdude) you can write Clojure too!
The documentation is at &lt;a href=&quot;https://logseq.github.io/#/page/60f5747e-6cb7-4216-b108-e60a93014590&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 14:10:19 GMT" tweetId="1417124647238135808" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1417124647238135808" inReplyToId="1417124186389049344" tweetUserName="logseq" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="You're on fire! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/manojnayak/status/1417111614667382784&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 14:07:06 GMT" tweetId="1417123837578072069" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1417123837578072069" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Awesome! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/manojnayak/status/1417094723899072516&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 12:18:11 GMT" tweetId="1417096427033939969" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1417096427033939969" tweetUserName="logseq" >
					<outline text="I also found this great publishing tutorial by @andrewshell, thank you!
&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=48isoMYjaR0&amp;ab_channel=AndrewShell&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 12:20:04 GMT" tweetId="1417096901460066304" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1417096901460066304" inReplyToId="1417096427033939969" tweetUserName="logseq" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Really exciting! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/flancian/status/1417052344924135426&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 10:43:55 GMT" tweetId="1417072705619202055" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1417072705619202055" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 18" type="calendarDay" name="18" >
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/k0sengan/status/1416279882858844160&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/tsgxzPDRrf" type="tweet" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 02:58:40 GMT" tweetId="1416955621958553603" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1416955621958553603" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Very cool! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/dasaptaerwin/status/1416320399474786308&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2021 02:56:29 GMT" tweetId="1416955070554333186" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1416955070554333186" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 16" type="calendarDay" name="16" >
				<outline text="Yes, you can still enjoy the flexibility and power of a graph database with both Markdown and Org-mode! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Bailey_Jennings/status/1415699063782129666&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 12:01:04 GMT" tweetId="1416004956511866888" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1416004956511866888" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 14" type="calendarDay" name="14" >
				<outline text="Thank you for considering us! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/agambrahma/status/1415184454151114752&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 19:49:00 GMT" tweetId="1415397940768612353" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1415397940768612353" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Thank you! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/cortexfutura/status/1415373568733503488&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 19:43:52 GMT" tweetId="1415396650072174592" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1415396650072174592" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="We just cut a new release (0.2.5) to fix this problem. Sorry for the trouble! Also, we made some changes that all the new deleted pages will be stored in `logseq/.recycle` so that you can still find them when you need to. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1415347503159934979&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 19:43:00 GMT" tweetId="1415396429644763136" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1415396429644763136" tweetUserName="logseq" >
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/logseq/logseq/releases/tag/0.2.5&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 19:43:18 GMT" tweetId="1415396506480234496" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1415396506480234496" inReplyToId="1415396429644763136" tweetUserName="logseq" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="We just received two reports that the new release can delete some pages when restarting, so we deleted the release, for those people who had upgraded to the new release, please stay on 0.2.3 until we find the cause and fix it, thank you!" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 16:28:35 GMT" tweetId="1415347503159934979" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1415347503159934979" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Afaik some users have more than 10 graphs. 😁 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/0x0decaf/status/1415340405642514438&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 16:05:01 GMT" tweetId="1415341572254691332" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1415341572254691332" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="0.2.4 is just out!
Some highlights:
- Block timestamps are brought back! It's disabled by default, you can enable it on the settings page
- &quot;All pages&quot; support sorting
- Publishing supports subpath &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1415332513543716865/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 15:29:01 GMT" tweetId="1415332513543716865" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1415332513543716865" tweetUserName="logseq" >
					<outline text="Full changelog at &lt;a href=&quot;https://logseq.github.io/#/page/60eef6a9-ad06-4a3e-99eb-7b093336ae68&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 15:33:14 GMT" tweetId="1415333575772180482" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1415333575772180482" inReplyToId="1415332513543716865" tweetUserName="logseq" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="I've been waiting for this for a long time! Finally, we can render queries as either tables or lists, the best thing is that the queries support both pages and blocks! 
Templates + Custom properties + Queries = You name it! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1415332057866067973/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 15:27:12 GMT" tweetId="1415332057866067973" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1415332057866067973" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 13" type="calendarDay" name="13" >
				<outline text="Thank you for the shoutout! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kylepulver/status/1414879436063657987&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 09:34:02 GMT" tweetId="1414880790991622147" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1414880790991622147" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 12" type="calendarDay" name="12" >
				<outline text="A good system is that we don't need to care where we write, and we can ask questions (queries) to get exactly what we need. That's one of the benefits of block-based (compared to files) and custom block properties. There's no limit on how you store and use your information! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ilmarsV/status/1414708312734580740&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 03:18:49 GMT" tweetId="1414786363099025408" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1414786363099025408" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="@douginamug thank you for your donation 🙏 - Your contribution means a lot to us!
&lt;a href=&quot;https://opencollective.com/logseq&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 01:29:07 GMT" tweetId="1414758758098653188" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1414758758098653188" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="@davewiner Glad to join the &quot;Communication with a big C&quot;!
https://t.co/v7nwDjXhou https://t.co/I1f0zVSFUn" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 14:20:31 GMT" tweetId="1414590499009093639" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1414590499009093639" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Thanks, Logseq doesn't and will not require a commercial license for both personal usage and company usage, as long as if the data are stored locally and doesn't use our server. The desktop is just like Vim and Emacs. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/xllora/status/1414529650009718785&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 12:59:53 GMT" tweetId="1414570206161031170" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1414570206161031170" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="For Markdown users, you can use @obsdmd's new mobile app with Logseq now, congrats!🎊
&lt;a href=&quot;https://discuss.logseq.com/t/making-obsidian-play-nice-with-logseq/1185&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/ffzlEIoAdA" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 08:53:11 GMT" tweetId="1414508125172822019" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1414508125172822019" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="It turns out Logseq is on GitHub trending now! 😱
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/trending&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/lShKMmcff0" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 07:17:34 GMT" tweetId="1414484059049238530" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1414484059049238530" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="We hope the community can bring the GitHub integration as a plugin in the future. In the meanwhile, we'll open-source the existing backend code this month for those users who'd like to self-host. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kunalbhalla/status/1414289513300512769&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 06:36:20 GMT" tweetId="1414473682953531392" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1414473682953531392" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 11" type="calendarDay" name="11" >
				<outline text="Unfortunately, we'll deprecate github integration when the mobile app is out for testing, it might be in 1-2 months. The mobile app will supports loading files from the local filesystem, which means we can still use iCloud, GDrive, Dropbox, etc. to sync our notes. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/k0sengan/status/1414279129931739136&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 17:49:03 GMT" tweetId="1414280592376569856" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1414280592376569856" tweetUserName="logseq" >
					<outline text="After that we'll build our own storage and collaboration." type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 17:50:09 GMT" tweetId="1414280868009373699" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1414280868009373699" inReplyToId="1414280592376569856" tweetUserName="logseq" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Me too! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/fioritto/status/1414272155039289351&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 17:18:46 GMT" tweetId="1414272970080456710" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1414272970080456710" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Welcome! I don't know we can run an AppImage on Chromebook, super cool! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/fioritto/status/1414270888028090368&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 17:17:34 GMT" tweetId="1414272667205529602" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1414272667205529602" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Thanks for trying us! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/xllora/status/1414247446356668418&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 16:09:00 GMT" tweetId="1414255410194747395" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1414255410194747395" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 9" type="calendarDay" name="09" >
				<outline text="page search preview thanks to @pengx17 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1413527639537577993&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/QnGaCH4xLh" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 16:12:31 GMT" tweetId="1413531522309652485" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1413531522309652485" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="a quick demo of the revamped graph which works well with huge repo! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1413527639537577993&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/u8mBGhkdPB" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 15:59:52 GMT" tweetId="1413528337423618050" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1413528337423618050" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Logseqers! Good Friday and 0.2.3 is just out!
Some highlights:
1. new shiny graph
2. page search preview
3. right-click a block bullet and export block as text or opml
4. enhanced document mode
5. new frameless look for desktop mac

full changelog:
&lt;a href=&quot;https://logseq.github.io/#/page/60e81184-6ec6-46fe-8456-5bb2480ab32c&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/z51mlyNyMN" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 15:57:05 GMT" tweetId="1413527639537577993" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1413527639537577993" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 6" type="calendarDay" name="06" >
				<outline text="Hi everyone, the beautiful queries and indentation from @OneStuttering! 🥳🥳
&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qQ8DzumRZkM&amp;ab_channel=OneStutteringMind&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/46ji2kk9Wn" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 05:56:48 GMT" tweetId="1412289406342373393" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1412289406342373393" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="@thezjy1 just uploaded a video on how to publish your logseq graph to the GitHub page! If you built a digital garden with Logseq, feel free to add yours to our community gardens &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/logseq/awesome-logseq#community-knowledge-gardens&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

https://t.co/CKs9hfDNTA

The documentation link:
https://t.co/ZO72aypO9w" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 05:29:22 GMT" tweetId="1412282503595847680" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1412282503595847680" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 5" type="calendarDay" name="05" >
				<outline text="Looks great! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/manojnayak/status/1411697632083275785&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 13:40:03 GMT" tweetId="1412043601907884036" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1412043601907884036" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 2" type="calendarDay" name="02" >
				<outline text="Wow, this website is published using Logseq! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Oscillations_1/status/1410961915157811206&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 15:39:21 GMT" tweetId="1410986460040208384" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1410986460040208384" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="June 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="june2021" >
			<outline text="June 30" type="calendarDay" name="30" >
				<outline text="Hello, friends of Logseq! What should we call a user of Logseq?" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 09:32:40 GMT" tweetId="1410169405036634120" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1410169405036634120" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 29" type="calendarDay" name="29" >
				<outline text="🥳 https://t.co/jHfVbk0hgL" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 02:25:27 GMT" tweetId="1410061890814824449" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1410061890814824449" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="0.2.2 is just out!
https://t.co/QAMiWg2IR3

Some highlights:
1. public pages not exported when publishing
2. images not working
3. dragging files might create duplicated files
4. @sebasbensu  allow numbers to have commas in `calculator`

Full changelog at https://t.co/DWvR7fFjNk https://t.co/DivbeuG40v" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:47:55 GMT" tweetId="1409901453494259715" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1409901453494259715" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Thanks! https://t.co/N6SyCwnpzV" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 07:44:29 GMT" tweetId="1409779793705402372" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1409779793705402372" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 28" type="calendarDay" name="28" >
				<outline text="@jihchi thank you for your donation 🙏 - Your contribution means a lot to us!
https://t.co/KGsf0HF97g" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 02:23:30 GMT" tweetId="1409699015168458752" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1409699015168458752" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="0.2.1 is just out! Some highlights:
1. Namespace pages now display with hierarchy
2. @devonzuegel polished and refactored setting and shortcut UI
3 @sebasbensu fixed codemirror click issue and improved calc parsing
4. Improved markdown/org link syntax behavior

full changelog: https://t.co/eMg4Kk2g9v" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 15:38:53 GMT" tweetId="1409536792475279363" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1409536792475279363" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 26" type="calendarDay" name="26" >
				<outline text="Thank you for the kind words! There are many inputs from the community and our contributors, glad to be more useful as a tool. https://t.co/fg6n1HozaP" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 17:26:17 GMT" tweetId="1408839044448985091" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1408839044448985091" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="😊 thank you! https://t.co/3NVM9gowUc" type="tweet" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2021 17:21:48 GMT" tweetId="1408837916529360896" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1408837916529360896" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 25" type="calendarDay" name="25" >
				<outline text="Thanks! https://t.co/0aziXfDl34" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 07:10:52 GMT" tweetId="1408321780276625408" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1408321780276625408" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 24" type="calendarDay" name="24" >
				<outline text="🥰 https://t.co/YPKoKgLf0w" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 08:33:13 GMT" tweetId="1407980117700222978" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1407980117700222978" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 23" type="calendarDay" name="23" >
				<outline text="0.2.0 is just out! Some highlights:
- Alt-dragging to create a block reference
- Configurable children level for linked references
- Customize shortcuts UI support
- @devonzuegel added a `/calculator` slash command
- @pengx17 added block children in preview
- Spanish support https://t.co/g8ORZrY1pF" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 14:13:37 GMT" tweetId="1407703393490010116" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1407703393490010116" tweetUserName="logseq" >
					<outline text="Full changelog at https://t.co/k6gr9cywhI" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 14:13:50 GMT" tweetId="1407703449970483206" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1407703449970483206" inReplyToId="1407703393490010116" tweetUserName="logseq" >
						<outline text="oops, the link should be https://t.co/icZi4Sk2Wu" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 14:33:20 GMT" tweetId="1407708353833226243" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1407708353833226243" inReplyToId="1407703449970483206" tweetUserName="logseq" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 21" type="calendarDay" name="21" >
				<outline text="Thanks! https://t.co/mDgOaQDjvn" type="tweet" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2021 03:11:55 GMT" tweetId="1407174481391480838" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1407174481391480838" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Wow, thank you very much for the kind words! We definitely need to improve a lot of things to pursue the future of information management! https://t.co/2trNzlaxoW" type="tweet" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2021 02:33:51 GMT" tweetId="1407164903245312000" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1407164903245312000" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="@volt4ire thank you for your donation 🙏 - Your contribution means a lot to us!
https://t.co/KGsf0HWKvQ" type="tweet" created="Mon, 21 Jun 2021 15:19:28 GMT" tweetId="1406995191005954052" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1406995191005954052" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 20" type="calendarDay" name="20" >
				<outline text="Super impressive! 🥳 Don't miss this one if you want more structured notes! https://t.co/nYnPZcgohN" type="tweet" created="Sun, 20 Jun 2021 14:12:47 GMT" tweetId="1406616020610023424" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1406616020610023424" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 19" type="calendarDay" name="19" >
				<outline text="Glad to know it works for you, thank you for the shout out! https://t.co/vwcjjs6SGq" type="tweet" created="Sat, 19 Jun 2021 12:02:49 GMT" tweetId="1406220926186754052" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1406220926186754052" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 18" type="calendarDay" name="18" >
				<outline text="Each [[page]] could be a community itself instead of just a page with some references. People can host their graphs everywhere and talk to each other. It'll be much better than how we learn and collaborate today!

- Our vision" type="tweet" created="Fri, 18 Jun 2021 17:13:09 GMT" tweetId="1405936634453921793" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1405936634453921793" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="Count us! 😂 https://t.co/xjL1hWhbDN" type="tweet" created="Fri, 18 Jun 2021 04:47:59 GMT" tweetId="1405749108183224321" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1405749108183224321" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 17" type="calendarDay" name="17" >
				<outline text="This can be the foundation for any Reader. Hopefully, someone will build a plugin soon. https://t.co/bprn3uR0oj" type="tweet" created="Thu, 17 Jun 2021 18:48:05 GMT" tweetId="1405598137985556481" urltweet="https://twitter.com/logseq/status/1405598137985556481" tweetUserName="logseq" />
				<outline text="A new plugin made by @xyhp915 for Reddit's hot news!
